goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?
goals.visualization: violin plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A violin plot can show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different categories.

goals.question: What is the trend in barley yield over time?
goals.visualization: line plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line plot can show the trend in yield over time, allowing for analysis of any patterns or changes in the data over the recorded years.

goals.question: Which site has the highest average yield of barley?
goals.visualization: bar chart of mean yield by site
goals.rationale: A bar chart can show the mean yield for each site, allowing for comparison of the central tendency of the data across different locations.

goals.question: Is there a relationship between barley yield and site location?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by site
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and site location, allowing for analysis of any patterns or correlations in the data.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='site', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    mean_yield_by_site = data.groupby('site')['yield'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='site', y='yield', data=mean_yield_by_site)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which site has the highest average yield of barley?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
